The Awareness Principle

	Philosophy

		-
			The awareness principle holds that, in an ideal world, people would know truth from
			falsehood, and would thus universally believe in the truth.
		-

	Principles

		The Reason Principle

			-
				The reason principle holds that people should be knowledgeable regarding the nature
				and underlying principles of the truths of reality, rather than believing in said
				truths on blind faith.
